'''Gillian Dorothy Kennedy''' {{post-nominal|unlinked=FRCSLT}} {{post nominals|UK|OBE}} is a Consultant [[speech and language therapist]] specialising in Neonates and Paediatrics at [[University College Hospital]].<ref name='UCHL'>{{cite web |url=https://www.uclh.nhs.uk/wwus/Whatstaffsay/Pages/QueenshonoursforGillian.aspx |title=Consultant - Gillian Kennedy |publisher=UCHL |accessdate=21 October 2018}}</ref>
==Career== Kennedy undertook undergraduate study at [[Edinburgh University]] and a MSc at [[City, University of London]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://apcp.csp.org.uk/content/way-babys-brain-through-their-stomach |title=‘The way to a baby’s brain is through their stomach’ |publisher=Association of Paediatric Chartered Psysiotherapists |accessdate=21 October 2018}}</ref> She is currently a Consultant [[speech and language therapist]] at University College Hospital and one of only two national trainers in NIDCAP (Newborn Individualised Developmental Care and Assessment Program). She teaches families and healthcare staff to recognise the importance of non-verbal communication in infants and is a national and international adviser and educator in the field.<ref name='UCHL' />
She was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists]] in 2015<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcslt.org/honours_roll_call_1945-2016 |title=RCSLT Honours Roll Call |publisher=Royal College of Speech and Lanuage Therapists |accessdate=21 October 2018}}</ref> and was awarded an OBE in the [[2015 Birthday Honours]] for services to Speech Therapy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jun/12/queens-birthday-honours-list-2015-obe |title=Queen's birthday honours list 2015: OBE. Order Of The British Empire, Civil: Office |date=12 June 2015 |publisher=The Guardian |accessdate=21 October 2018}}</ref>
