'''Hypocementosis''' is a reduction in the amount of [[cementum]] on a [[tooth]] root. It is a feature of conditions such as [[cleidocranial dysplasia]] and [[hypophosphatasia]].<ref name="Ireland2010">{{cite book|author=Ireland R|title=A Dictionary of Dentistry|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XWCcAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA180|date=25 March 2010|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-953301-5|page=180}}</ref>

