The '''National Disabled Women's Educational Equity Project''' was established by [[Corbett O'Toole]] in Berkeley, California in 1980.<ref name="Timeline">{{cite web | url = http://isc.temple.edu/neighbor/ds/disabilityrightstimeline.htm | title = Disability History Timeline | year = 2002 | work = Rehabilitation Research & Training Center on Independent Living Management | publisher = [[Temple University]] | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131220065328/http://isc.temple.edu/neighbor/ds/disabilityrightstimeline.htm | archivedate = 2013-12-20 | df =  }}</ref> It was a three-year research and demonstration project.<ref name="google.com">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BmHJBC4SUBsC&q=%22disabled+women%27s+educational+equity+project%22&dq=%22disabled+women%27s+educational+equity+project%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=IWfGVMK9J4ergwTut4LQCA&ved=0CEAQ6wEwBQ|title=Departments of Labor, Health and Human Services, Education, and related ... - United States. Congress. House. Committee on Appropriations. Subcommittee on the Departments of Labor, Health and Human Services, Education, and Related Agencies - Google Books|work=google.com}}</ref> Based at the [[Disability Rights Education and Defense Fund]] (DREDF), the Project administered the first national survey on disability and gender.<ref name="Timeline"/> It also conducted the first national Conference on Disabled Women's Educational Equity, which was held in Bethesda, Maryland.<ref name="FAANAHN-BC2009">{{cite book|author1=Dr. Rozzano C. Locsin RN, PhD, FAAN|author2=Dr. Marguerite Purnell RN, PhD, AHN-BC|title=A Contemporary Nursing Process: The (Un)Bearable Weight of Knowing in Nursing|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=plYc5I8D3YoC&pg=PA308|date=10 April 2009|publisher=Springer Publishing Company|isbn=978-0-8261-2579-8|pages=308–}}</ref> It developed written materials for educators and counselors relevant to the needs of disabled women and girls.<ref name="google.com"/> It also developed a book about role models for disabled teenage girls called ''No More Stares.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/search?tbm=bks&hl=en&q=%22disabled+women%27s+educational+equity+project%22|title="disabled women's educational equity project" - Google Search|work=google.com}}</ref>

